load data

Pm_data<-read.csv("./exp-data/Re_mapped_exp.csv")

keep<-reshape::melt(Pm_data, id="target_id") %>% group_by(target_id) %>% 
  summarize(tpm = mean(value)) %>% filter(tpm >=0.5) %>% dplyr::select(target_id) #filter genes with mean<0.5 in all libs

tpmKeep<-Pm_data %>% filter(target_id %in% keep$target_id) %>% column_to_rownames('target_id')


factors<-data.frame(Tissue = c(rep("venom_gland",28),rep("heart",4),rep("kidney",4),rep("liver",4),rep("new_venom_gland",4)), lib = c(colnames(tpmKeep)))

diagnostics

design<-model.matrix(~0+factor(Tissue),factors)
rownames(design)<-factors$lib

dge<-DGEList(tpmKeep)
dge<-calcNormFactors(dge)
mds <- plotMDS(dge)

rlog_trans <- rlog(as.matrix(round(tpmKeep)))
rlog_trans %>% saveRDS("./rlog_trans.RDS")
rlog_trans<-readRDS("./rlog_trans.RDS")
se<-SummarizedExperiment(rlog_trans - rowMeans(rlog_trans),colData=factors)
pcaData <- plotPCA(DESeqTransform(se), intgroup=c("Tissue", "lib"),ntop = 1000, returnData=TRUE) #becomes progressively worse when increasing ntop
percentVar_all <- round(100 * attr(pcaData, "percentVar"))
names(pcaData)[c(4,5)] = c('Tissue',"Lib")


ggplot(pcaData, aes(PC1, PC2, color=Tissue)) +
  geom_point(size=3,alpha = 1)

Correlation btween new venom libraries and old ones

venom_only<-select(tpmKeep,!c(Pm_1_hrt,Pm_5_hrt,Pm_3_hrt,Pm_8_hrt,Pm_1_kid,Pm_3_kid,Pm_5_kid,Pm_8_kid,
                  Pm_1_livr,Pm_3_livr,Pm_5_livr,Pm_8_livr))
dat<-venom_only %>% rownames_to_column("gene_id") %>% group_by(gene_id) %>% 
  summarise(old_lib=mean(Pm_3:Pm_30),new_lib = mean(new_Pm1_f:new_Pm4_f)) %>% filter(c(old_lib >=0.05),new_lib>=0.05)


cor.test(log(dat$old_lib),log(dat$new_lib), method = "spearman")
